line_1: He loudly bellows out his patriot speeches;
line_2: Now in crop'd greasy hair, and leather breeches,

line_1: And greets His Wife with angry Speeches;
line_2: If She be seen without her Breeches.

line_1: Rough Satyrs, sly Remarks, ill-natur'd Speeches,
line_2: Are always aim'd at Poets, that wear Breeches.

line_1: Bow'd round, — and, full of soothing speeches
line_2: (Quick through the ear their credence reaches)
Brake forth the prophet without breeches.
Thus, having first pull'd up his breeches,

line_1: She hears with dignity their speeches,
